The tsunami Warning continues in effect for the coastal areas of California from the California-Mexico border to Ragged Point, California (45 miles NW of San Luis Obispo). - Event details: Preliminary magnitude 8.4 (Ml) earthquake / Lat: 32.776, Lon: -115.633 at 2012-09-17T23:53:57Z Tsunami warnings mean that a tsunami with significant widespread inundation is expected, or occurring. Warnings indicate that widespread dangerous coastal flooding accompanied by powerful currents is possible and may continue for several hours after the initial wave arrival. Recommended Actions: People in low-lying coastal areas should be alert to instructions from their local emergency officials. Evacuations are only ordered by emergency response agencies. If in a tsunami warning coastal area, move inland to higher ground. If in a tsunami advisory coastal area, move out of the water, off the beach, and out of harbors and marinas. If in a tsunami watch coastal area, stay alert for supplemental information. Next update and additional information: This message will be updated in 30 minutes or sooner if the situation warrants. The tsunami message will remain in effect until further notice.
